results.name: Number of nonsquarefree numbers in the reduced residue system of n.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: n=15, there are A000010(15)=8 residues: 1, 2, 4=2^2, 7, 8=2^3, 11, 13 and 14; two of them are not squarefree: 4 and 8, therefore a(15)=2.
mathematica: a[n_] := EulerPhi[n] - Module[{rad = Times @@ (First@# & /@ FactorInteger[n])}, Sum[MoebiusMu[k*rad]^2, {k, 1, n}]]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 08 2020 *)
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jul 25 2002
